reviews.reviewText: I typically pay attention to ratings and recently have also been paying attention to dimensions. Sadly, I forgot to pay attention to the size of the dresser before I bought it. It's so snall!!! I'm only 5'4" and feel like I'm bending down way too much just to use the top drawer! Haha It makes me feel like a giant. I recommend for a tiny place or for a small child. I usually love putting furniture together but this dresser was a bit frustrating. The screws to the handles wouldn't go in straight, or all the way, so I ended up having to super glue them on. Thankfully I can put this in my daughter's room and get myself something bugger and more suitable for my needs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars This is a VERY small dresser and some pictures have been manipulated
reviews.reviewText: First, I want to say that the company did give me a $60 refund, and I am appreciative of the customer service on that end.However, many pictures in this listing are misleading. This is not untreated wood. It's manufactured, plasticky wood just like any other cheap dresser online. Second, while the pictures may make this look like a normal sized dresser, particularly in the one made to look like a baby's room, that is not at all the case. If you look closely you can see that pic has been photoshopped. This dresser is only 29.5" high, so make sure you measure that. I'll be selling it because return shipping isn't covered.
